<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>When in a social situation with someone im not super comfortable with i will just cut my emotions down to %10 (dunno how else to describe it) and just keep my mouth shout only saying what needs to be said.</p> <p>However i find this extremely draining and if i do it for long periods of time get shaky / anxious etc.</p> <p>EDIT: Hey i cant be completely useless, made it to the top of <a href="/r/adhd">/r/adhd</a>! EDIT*: No for real though i thought i was one of the few people who did this cant believe how many of you have experienced such similar things to me i have learned allot thanks everyone your all awesome!</p> <p>Anybody else finding themselves needing to tone down their personality so they get accepted?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/GlassyPurpleBlock"> /u/GlassyPurpleBlock </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/ADHD/comments/bwi9um/anybody_find_themselves_having_to_actively_mute/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/ADHD/comments/bwi9um/anybody_find_themselves_having_to_actively_mute/">[comments]</a></span>